node.text:
Water is a valuable resource across the planet Earth. In Madeira it is a resource of
extreme importance, as it is born in the immaculate nature in the north of the island and it’s transported to the south, through the historic levadas.
.
Today, on World Water Day, we honor this essential resource for life and those who, daily, work to bring it from nature to our homes. It is a long and hard journey that
needs to be valued and respected.

@ar.madeira 
@governoregionaldamadeira 
#WorldWaterDay
#DiaMundialdaÁgua
#Madeira

They call it the TOUGHEST hike in HONG KONG. It's the West Dog's Teeth Ridge Trail. It sounded like the perfect place to test out the @djiglobal #OsmoAction for the entire journey from start to summit. It was a big bloody adventure and the camera impressed me throughout. My favorite features are the RockSteady, which does a great job stabilizing the footage even when I'm running on a rocky ridge. I also loved the dual-screen, which means when you can see exactly what you are filming when the camera is pointed at you. COMMENT BELOW what is the toughest hike you've ever done!? -

Shot on the @djiglobal #OsmoAction. See my stories for some insight into why this camera is an awesome tool for capturing real adventures. #sponsored

node.text:
Tomorrow a new adventure begins! I'm setting off on a 3-week expedition to climb Spantik Peak in Pakistan, which has a summit of 7,027m. It's the golden peak in this photo, which you can see in the distance 💫 This expedition will be a challenge but I'm ready for the unknown and to test myself at new heights. I'll be off-grid from the 7th until we return later this month #Pakistan #Hunza #Spantik
.
This photo was taken at Eagle's Nest 🦅 in Hunza, where you find beautiful views of Spantik and other 7000m peaks in the region. Thanks @joao_lets_hike for hiking out to the viewpoint and adding some scale to the photo 🤜🏽
.
On tour with @epicbackpackertours

node.text:
Dreaming wide awake in the mountains of Pakistan 🇵🇰 💫 This amazing sunset view was from in between Passu Glacier and Batura Glacier in Patundas. The trek to get here was a 3-day expedition to 4,800m with @epicbackpackertours 🦅 We crossed glaciers, gained 2000m of elevation and clocked 30km on this incredible camping trip that was one of my favorites of 2021! Always grateful for these adventures and hope they never end 🙏🏽 #Pakistan 
.
Thanks for the photo @off_the_atlas

Long arduous days on rocky glaciers en route to K2 Basecamp in Pakistan 🇵🇰 This trek with @epicbackpackertours was 170km with almost 10,000m of vertical gain. It didn't take us long to learn that glacier water has magic healing properties to recover our muscles and keep us going day after day ❄️ @epicbackpackertours next K2 basecamp trek is in 2022. You can hit the link in my bio to register your interest. #Pakistan #K2Basecamp #K2BasecampTrek
.

We're the only ones out here looking over the Batura Glacier, one of the longest in the world ❄️ It takes two days to hike up to this ridge and apart from a few wild Ibex, it felt as if we were exploring the unknown. Pakistan has felt a lot like that. Wild landscapes with no-one else in sight. It's hard to know which way to look with a glacier on either side and 7000m peaks towering above you. It's hard not to love this land 🇵🇰 #Pakistan
.
Shot on @insta360 OneX2 360 Camera #insta360 #Insta360OneX2 
.

node.text:
High in the mountains the mind roams further than my feet. No distractions but mighty peaks, no responsibilities but moving forward. One foot in front of the other day in, day out. It's a simple existence up here, the complexities of life are left behind for now. We begin to appreciate small things. Fresh water, morning sun, a warm cup of soup after a long day. I'm full of gratitude for these mountains that bring out the best in me. I'll be back before too long. 
.

The K2 Basecamp Trek is a challenging hike but what makes this such a special route are the campsites. Each night we slept beneath the monolithic mountains of 7000m and 8000m often hearing avalanches on the slopes nearby. Here's a small sample of some of my favorite campsites from the trek including K2 Basecamp, Concordia and Khoburtse. Which one looks like the best campsite to you?
